            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "From IRC:\r\n\r\n```\r\n<davidism> mitsuhiko am I right in saying that --debug can be added back to the cli but --app can't? https://github.com/pallets/flask/issues/2292\r\n<mitsuhiko> davidism: right now i do not remember the details but i did not find a way to reconfigure click itself early enough based on parameters\r\n<mitsuhiko> which means if --app is able to change the app then commands in click that would be available through the app might not be loaded in all situations\r\n<mitsuhiko> --debug probably is fine if we are happy to flip the flag late\r\n<mitsuhiko> eg: it would only be changed later when the server boots\r\n<mitsuhiko> but it would have issues setting the initial value of debug\r\n<davidism> Hmm, since the reloader and debbuger are enabled based on the debug flag, it's probably still safer to leave it as an env var until Click fixes things.\r\n```"
